<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Armstrong</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-25"><hi rend="italic">May 25,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister for foreign affairs informs me that all contracts for Cuban leaf
                            tobacco entered into before publication of order prohibiting its
                            exportation are to be respected and that suggestion in your telegram of
                            22d has been anticipated.</p>
                        <p>Order of the minister for the colonies to Governor-General dated the 8th
                            instant and repeated by telegraph to-day.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Armstrong</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chargé.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>